column19: fajr start time is according to latest of three sites (Highfields this year)
suhur end is just 3 minutes before this
this means that at the other sites fajr actually starts in between these 2 times on some days
IS THERE ANY NEED TO HAVE SEPARATE TIMES? Wifaq's timetable has a fixed time for every year anyway.
###### Will be easier just to stick to Fajr time with a precautionary note #####
Update 2022. Yes. Ihtiyaat dictates that we have 2 times. Fajr start will be preceeded by 5min suhuur ends

column2: Zuhr & Jumma Salaah will take place at 1.30pm (Jumma talk will start at 1pm followed by the Khutbah at 1:25pm)
The start of Islamic months are subject to sighting of the new moon
